The '''Ghana national football team''' represents [[Ghana]] in men's international [[Association football|football]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Black Stars|url=https://www.ghanafa.org/category/black-stars|work=Ghana Football Association|language=en|access-date=22 May 2020|archive-date=23 May 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200523044246/https://www.ghanafa.org/category/black-stars|url-status=live}}</ref> The team is named the '''Black Stars''' after the [[Black Star of Africa]] in the [[flag of Ghana]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ghana Flag Ghana High Commission |url=https://www.ghanahighcommissionuk.com/ghanaflag.aspx |access-date=2023-07-19 |website=Brazil Consulate}}</ref> It is governed by the [[Ghana Football Association]], the governing body for [[football in Ghana]].<ref>{{cite web | title=Ghana Football Association, Biography | url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/person/Ghana-Football-Association-3586 }}</ref> Prior to 1957, it played as the [[Gold Coast (British colony)|Gold Coast]].<ref>{{cite web | title=Black Stars, Biography | url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/person/Black-Stars-3622 }}</ref>

Ghana qualified for the [[FIFA World Cup]] for the first time in [[2006 FIFA World Cup|2006]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-09-07 |title=How Ghana has started every World Cup qualifying campaign since Germany 2006 run |url=https://citisportsonline.com/2021/09/07/how-ghana-have-started-every-world-cup-qualifying-campaign-since-germany-2006-run/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230616201334/https://citisportsonline.com/2021/09/07/how-ghana-have-started-every-world-cup-qualifying-campaign-since-germany-2006-run/ |archive-date=16 June 2023 |access-date=2023-06-16 |website=Citi Sports Online |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-05-18 |title='I knew I would score against Czech Republic' – Asamoah Gyan on 2006 World Cup goal |url=https://citisportsonline.com/2022/05/18/i-knew-i-would-score-against-czech-republic-asamoah-gyan-on-2006-world-cup-goal/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230616201334/https://citisportsonline.com/2022/05/18/i-knew-i-would-score-against-czech-republic-asamoah-gyan-on-2006-world-cup-goal/ |archive-date=16 June 2023 |access-date=2023-06-16 |website=Citi Sports Online |language=en-US}}</ref> The team has won the [[Africa Cup of Nations]] four times ([[1963 African Cup of Nations|1963]], [[1965 African Cup of Nations|1965]], [[1978 African Cup of Nations|1978]], and [[1982 African Cup of Nations|1982]]), while finishing as runners-up five times ([[1968 African Cup of Nations|1968]], [[1970 African Cup of Nations|1970]], [[1992 African Cup of Nations|1992]], [[2010 Africa Cup of Nations|2010]], and [[2015 Africa Cup of Nations|2015]]).<ref>{{cite web | url=https://teamghanaeu.com/our-history/ | title=Our History }}</ref> They have also qualified for the [[African Nations Championship|CHAN]] four times, finishing as runners-up twice ([[2009 African Nations Championship|2009]] and [[2014 African Nations Championship|2014]]).<ref>{{cite news | date=16 January 2004 | url=https://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/africa/3396199.stm | title=African Football: The early years | work=BBC | access-date=16 January 2004 | archive-date=24 January 2004 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20040124113449/http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/africa/3396199.stm | url-status=live }}</ref>

In 2009, Ghana achieved a historic milestone by becoming the first African nation to win the FIFA U-20 World Cup, defeating Brazil in the final in Egypt.<ref>{{cite web |title=Every FIFA U-20 World Cup final – Ghana champions 2009 |url=https://www.fifa.com/en/tournaments/mens/u20worldcup/chile-2025/articles/every-u-20-world-cup-winner-argentina-brazil-france-messi-maradona |website=FIFA.com |access-date=15 January 2026}}</ref>

As at November 20, 2025, Ghana ranked 72nd in the world and 17th among African football nations.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-11-19 |title=Ghana's Black Stars climb up in FIFA Rankings despite recent losses to Japan & South Korea - Citi Sports Online |url=https://citisportsonline.com/2025/11/ghanas-black-stars-climb-up-in-fifa-rankings-despite-recent-losses-to-japan-south-korea/ |access-date=2025-11-20 |language=en-US}}</ref>